'''Santiago Ignacio Bueno Sciutto''' (born 9 November 1998) is a Uruguayan professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for {{English football updater|WolverhW}} club [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] and the [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay national team]].

==Club career==
===Peñarol===
Born in [[Montevideo]], Bueno joined [[Peñarol]] in 2009, aged ten.<ref name="TF">{{cite web|url=https://www.tenfield.com.uy/santiago-bueno-17-anos-el-defensor-de-futuro-en-zaguero-me-convirtio-perdomo-y-sueno-con-debutar-en-el-campeon-del-siglo/|title=Santiago Bueno, 17 años, el defensor del futuro: "Zaguero me convirtió Perdomo; sueño debutar en el Campeón del Siglo"|trans-title=Santiago Bueno, 17-years-old, the defender of the future: "Perdomo converted me into a centre-back; I dream of making the debut at the Campeón del Siglo"|publisher=[[Tenfield]]|language=es|date=3 July 2016|access-date=12 September 2019}}</ref> On 5 January 2016, he was promoted to the first team squad.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tenfield.com.uy/acuerdo-por-freitas-costa-cerca/|title=Savia nueva en Peñarol|trans-title=Young blood at Peñarol|publisher=Tenfield|language=es|date=5 January 2016|access-date=12 September 2019}}</ref>

Bueno made his unofficial first team debut on 23 January 2016, playing the entire second-half of a 1–1 draw against [[Club Libertad]] in the Copa Antel [[Exhibition match|friendly]] tournament.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.xn--pearol-xwa.org/uc_4099_1.html|title=Santiago Bueno hizo su estreno en Primera|trans-title=Santiago Bueno made his debut in ''Primera''|publisher=CA Peñarol|language=es|date=24 January 2016|access-date=12 September 2019|archive-date=21 July 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200721045018/http://www.xn--pearol-xwa.org/uc_4099_1.html|url-status=dead}}</ref>

===Barcelona===
On 31 January 2017, [[FC Barcelona]] reached an agreement with Peñarol for the transfer of Bueno. He signed a two-and-a-half-year contract with the [[Catalonia|Catalans]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fcbarcelona.cat/futbol/juvenil-a/noticies/2016-2017/acord-amb-el-ca-penarol-pel-traspas-de-santiago-bueno|title=Acord amb el CA Peñarol pel traspàs de Santiago Bueno|trans-title=Agreement with CA Peñarol for the transfer of Santiago Bueno|publisher=FC Barcelona|language=ca|date=31 January 2017|access-date=12 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/fc-barcelona/cantera/20170214/4219979134/santiago-bueno-llega-a-barcelona-para-quedarse-toda-la-vida.html|title=Santiago Bueno llega a Barcelona para quedarse "toda la vida"|date=14 February 2017|access-date=18 February 2017|author=Javier de León|language=Spanish|work=Mundo Deportivo}}</ref> Barcelona had followed his progress for a year before signing him.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/fc-barcelona/cantera/20170202/413904388073/un-ano-siguiendo-a-santiago-bueno.html|title=Un año detrás de Santiago Bueno|date=3 February 2017|access-date=7 March 2017|author=Ferran Martínez|language=Spanish|work=Mundo Deportivo}}</ref>

====Peralada (loans)====
On 24 January 2018, Bueno was loaned to [[Segunda División B]] side [[CF Peralada-Girona B]] until the end of [[2017–18 Segunda División B|the season]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fcbarcelona.cat/ca/noticies/724339/acord-amb-el-cf-peralada-girona-b-per-a-la-cessio-de-santi-bueno|title=Acord amb el CF Peralada-Girona B per a la cessió de Santi Bueno|trans-title=Agreement with CF Peralada-Girona B for the loan of Santi Bueno|publisher=FC Barcelona|language=ca|date=24 January 2018|access-date=13 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.emporda.info/esports/2018/01/24/bueno-reforca-defensa-dun-peralada/380962.html|title=Bueno reforça la defensa d'un Peralada-Girona B que també lliga el porter Marc Vito|date=25 January 2018|access-date=4 February 2018|language=Spanish|publisher=Emporda}}</ref> He returned to the side on 31 August 2018, for a second loan spell.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/fc-barcelona/20180831/451547248244/oficial-santi-bueno-otra-vez-del-barca-b-al-peralada.html|title=Oficial: Santi Bueno, otra vez del Barça B al Peralada|trans-title=Official: Santi Bueno, again from ''Barça'' B to Peralada|work=[[Mundo Deportivo]]|language=es|date=31 August 2018|access-date=13 September 2019}}</ref>

===Girona===
On 19 August 2019, Bueno signed a five-year contract with [[Girona FC]] in the second division, as a [[free agent]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.futbol.com.uy/Deportes/Espana-Girona-incorporo-a-Santiago-Bueno-como-jugador-libre-tras-dejar-Barcelona-uc727453|title=España: Girona incorporó a Santiago Bueno como jugador libre tras dejar Barcelona|website=futbol.com.uy – Montevideo Portal}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.elobservador.com.uy/nota/santiago-bueno-del-sueno-de-barcelona-a-girona-201982092853|title=Santiago Bueno, del sueño de Barcelona a Girona|first=El|last=Observador|website=El Observador}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gironafc.cat/es/noticia/santi-bueno-nuevo-refuerzo-para-la-defensa-del-girona-fc|title=Santi Bueno, nuevo refuerzo para la defensa del Girona FC|trans-title=Santi Bueno, new addition for Girona FC's defense|publisher=Girona FC|language=es|date=19 August 2019|access-date=13 September 2019}}</ref> He made his debut for the club on 19 December, starting in a 2–1 away win against [[Linares Deportivo]] in [[2019–20 Copa del Rey|that season's Copa del Rey]].<ref name="prodebut">{{cite web|title=LINARES DEPORTIVO VS. GIRONA 1 – 2|url=https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2019/12/19/spain/copa-del-rey/linares-deportivo/girona-fc/3185265/|access-date=21 December 2019}}</ref>

Bueno made his professional debut on 20 July 2020, coming on as a late [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Christian Rivera (Spanish footballer)|Christian Rivera]] in a 2–0 loss at [[AD Alcorcón]] in the [[Segunda División]] championship.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/segunda-division/cronica/2020/07/20/5f15c6c8e2704e171c8b45a7.html|title=El Alcorcón despide el año con un cumpleaños muy feliz|trans-title=Alcorcón end the year with a very happy birthday|work=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|language=es|date=20 July 2020|access-date=20 July 2020}}</ref> He scored his first professional goal on 10 April 2021, but in a 2–1 loss at [[Rayo Vallecano]], and was a regular starter during the [[2021–22 Segunda División|2021–22 season]] as the club achieved promotion to [[La Liga]].

Bueno made his debut in the Spanish top tier on 14 August 2022, starting in a 1–0 away loss to [[Valencia CF]]. The following 23 January, he renewed his contract until 2026.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gironafc.cat/es/noticias/santi-bueno-renueva-hasta-el-2026|title=Santi Bueno renueva hasta el 2026|trans-title=Santi Bueno renews until 2026|publisher=Girona FC|language=es|date=23 January 2023|accessdate=30 August 2023}}</ref>

===Wolverhampton Wanderers===
On 30 August 2023, Bueno underwent a medical for a transfer to English club [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66657986|title=Uruguay defender Bueno to have Wolves medical|work=BBC Sport|date=30 August 2023}}</ref> A day later, he officially joined the club for a reported £8.5&nbsp;million fee, signing a five-year contract.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Stone |first=Simon |date=31 August 2023 |title=Wolves complete signing of Uruguay defender Bueno |language=en-GB |work=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66675097 |access-date=31 August 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wolves.co.uk/news/mens-first-team/20230831-bueno-latest-through-the-door/|title=Bueno latest through the door|publisher= Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|date=31 August 2023|access-date=31 August 2023}}</ref>

Bueno made his Wolves debut in an [[EFL Cup]] game away to [[Ipswich Town F.C.|Ipswich Town]] on 26 September 2023.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/66850677|title=Ipswich Town 3–2 Wolverhampton Wanderers: Championship high-flyers stun Premier League side in Carabao Cup|work=BBC Sport |date=26 September 2023 |access-date=30 November 2023}}</ref>

Bueno made his Premier League debut in a controversial 3–2 defeat away to [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]] on 27 November 2023 that featured three penalties.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/67470815|title=Fulham 3–2 Wolves: Two Willian penalties help Cottagers snatch win amid VAR controversy|work=BBC Sport |last=Rindl |first=Joe |date=27 November 2023 |access-date=30 November 2023}}</ref> 

On 27 September 2025, he scored his first goal for the club and first ever Premier League goal in a 1–1 draw with [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Smyth |first=Rob |date=27 September 2025 |title=Tottenham 1-1 Wolves: Premier League – as it happened |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2025/sep/27/tottenham-v-wolves-premier-league-live |access-date=27 September 2025 |work=the Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref>  

==International career==
[[File:Santiago_Ignacio_Bueno.jpg|thumb|right|150px|Bueno with the Uruguay under-20 team in 2017]]Bueno has represented Uruguay at [[Uruguay national under-17 football team|under-17]] and [[Uruguay national under-20 football team|under-20]] youth international levels.<ref name="auf">{{cite web|title=2 – Santiago Bueno – AUF|url=https://www.auf.org.uy/2-santiago-bueno/|access-date=16 July 2020}}</ref><ref name = "SW"/> In December 2019, he was called up to the [[Uruguay Olympic football team|under-23 team]] for the [[2020 CONMEBOL Pre-Olympic Tournament]].<ref>{{cite web|title=25 convocados a la preselección olímpica|url=https://www.auf.org.uy/25-convocados-a-la-preseleccion-olimpica/|access-date=22 December 2019}}</ref>

On 21 October 2022, Bueno was named in Uruguay's 55-man preliminary squad for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Selección: Diego Alonso entregó la lista de 55 reservados para el Mundial de Catar|url=https://www.futbol.com.uy/Deportes/Seleccion-Diego-Alonso-entrego-la-lista-de-55-reservados-para-el-Mundial-de-Catar-uc835965|date=21 October 2022|access-date=21 October 2022|language=es}}</ref> but did not make it to the final squad. He made his debut with [[Uruguay national football team|the full side]] on 24 March 2023, starting in a 1–1 [[Exhibition match|friendly]] draw against [[Japan national football team|Japan]] at the [[Japan National Stadium]] in Tokyo.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com.ar/futbol/mundial/nota/_/id/11802337/seleccion-uruguaya-analisis-debut-estreno-santiago-bueno|title=Fue sobrio, no se complicó e inició la acción del gol: el debut de Santiago Bueno en Uruguay|trans-title=He was serious, did not complicate himself and started the goal play: the debut of Santiago Bueno with Uruguay|publisher=[[ESPN]]|language=es|date=24 March 2023|accessdate=30 August 2023}}</ref> On 31 May 2026, he was named in Uruguay's 26-man squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Mundial 2026: Uruguay dio a conocer la lista de 26 convocados por Marcelo Bielsa|url=https://www.montevideo.com.uy/Deportes/Mundial-2026-Uruguay-dio-a-conocer-la-lista-de-26-convocados-por-Marcelo-Bielsa-uc963756|language=es|date=31 May 2026|access-date=31 May 2026}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Bueno is the younger brother of professional footballer [[Gastón Bueno]].<ref name=TF/> His cousin [[Gonzalo Bueno (footballer)|Gonzalo Bueno]] is a former Uruguayan youth international.<ref name=TF/>

